tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and mildly high albumin, ALT, total cholesterol, and LDL cholesterol. Other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation for possible chronic kidney disease, monitoring of liver function, and cardiovascular risk assessment. No acute abnormalities detected.
